                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>The autosampler parameters (CTC PAL Dual Head Autosampler) were as follows: Sample Volume, 1 \u00b5L; Solvent A/B Post Wash, 5 (n-hexane, isopropanol). The GC parameters (Agilent 7890 Gas Chromatograph) were as follows: Column, DB5 column 30 m + 10 m DG pre-column, 0.25 mm, 0.25 \u00b5m, Agilent; Front Inlet Mode, Splitless;&nbsp;Front Inlet &amp; Transfer Line Temp, 250 \u00b0C;&nbsp;Front Inlet Septum Purge Flow, 3 mL/min,&nbsp;Front Inlet Purge Time, 1 min;&nbsp;Front Inlet Purge Flow, 40 mL/min;&nbsp;Front Inlet Total Flow, 42.2 mL/min;&nbsp;Target Flow, 2.2 mL/min (Constant Flow);&nbsp;Oven Temperature Ramp, 60 (Duration: 1 min) to 325 (Duration: 10 min) at 10 \u00b0C/min; GC Method Total Time, 37.5 min.</p><p><br></p><p>The derivatized samples were analyzed in a randomized order and MSTFA blanks were ran every 4th sample. RI samples containing MSTFA and the C7-C30 saturated alkanes (1000 \u03bcg/mL, Supelco) were placed before and after each run.</p>",
